        "title": "First attempt to learn about Intent",
        "body": "<p>I have a button on Main's android xml file which once clicked will display another view/activity. \nMy problem is the error message displays that the application must end unexpectedly.<\/p>\n\n<p>Here is the button <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Button android:id=\"@+id/showmeurcode\"\n   android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n   android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n   android:onClick=\"OnShowMeUrCode\"\n&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The method OnShowMeUrCode is defined in the MainActivity class as<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private void OnShowMeUrCode(View btn)\n{\n    Intent urCode=new Intent(this,CodePage.class);\n    startActivity(urCode);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><code>CodePage<\/code> is generated from a class of the same name <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class CodePage extends Activity\n{\n   ....\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>That is all I have done in the hope that I could accomplish the simple task with Intent to display another view but I run in an unexpected error and my program fails short.<\/p>\n",
