            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1349213284,
            "creation_date": 1349213284,
            "body": "<p>Based on your code without the error log output, I guess you didn't pass a correct Context to the method.<\/p>\n\n<p>This is your code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private void OnShowMeUrCode(View btn)\n{\n    Intent urCode=new Intent(this,CodePage.class);\n    startActivity(urCode);\n}  \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Try replace the relevant line with:<\/p>\n\n<p><code>Intent urCode=new Intent(MainActivity.this,CodePage.class);<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>Say, I have two Activities, A and B. If I'm calling B from A, I should write something like:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Intent i = new Intent(A.this, B.class);\nstartActivity(i);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Besides, you need to register your Activity in AndroidManifest.xml each time you create a new activity. In your case, please check if there are 2 activities in your AndroidManifest.xml<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 12698598,
            "question_id": 12698487
        }
